    Trade remains crucial to Australia’s prosperity. Our exports have helped to
    fuel China’s rapid growth while in turn we import a bevy of items, among
    them cars, petroleum and computers, from around the world. Ensuring our
    ongoing freedom of trade is an important element of Australian foreign
    policy.

